-- Damas International Sets Value of Gold Taken by Founders at $69.7 Million
-- B y   I n a l   E r s a n
-- 2010-10-28T06:29:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/damas-international-sets-value-of-gold-taken-by-founders-at-69-7-million.html
Damas International said it agreed
with its founders, the Abdullah bothers, to value gold they had
withdrawn from the company at 256 million dirhams ($69.7
million), according to a statement to the Nasdaq Dubai bourse
today.  The Abdullah brothers also owe the company 358 million
dirhams in cash, the company said. The two sides agreed to
extend the deadline for the payment of 400 million dirhams by
the brothers until Jan. 31, from Oct. 31, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Inal Ersan in Dubai at 
